B07lab5

Overview
In this lab we create two new classes of shapes, Quadrilateral and Circle, consisting of a type of manipulation of a two dimensional shape.

Features
Circle:
Create a circle by specifying its center and tangent point
Calulate the radius and diameter of the circle
Calculate the area of the circle using its radius
Calculate the circumference of the circle using its radius

Quadrilateral:
Create a quadrilateral with repect to four ordered points A,B,C and D
Calulate perimeter of the quadrilateral
Judge whether the specific quadrilateral is a parallelogram, a rectangle, a rhombus or a square

Collaborators: Jeong Yuseon, Vanessa Schattman, Hanji Zhang , Yixi Li, and Lingke Meng
